column5: Action was slow, weather was good, that's fishin'.  Great job Mau  Here are some shots:    Lots of cars in the parking lot and on the ice.     MuskyBill and Glen             Workin' the fire. They caught as many fish as I did.   Great prizes, I think everybody got something.         Can't hide him anywhere.    Thanks gang!!!
Wow.  The ice looks absolutely perfect for driving on.
Great pics as usual Rob.  It was nice to see everyone today.
I looked for you.  Nice collection of pics bud.  As for the bearded guy,you will never hide him,unless he is down in the Mississippi swamps.LOL
Looks like it was a great event. Maybe next year it won't coincide with the Spring Fishing Show, that way more people can attend for such a great cause....Congrats!!  Dirk..
Bunch of great photos!  Thanks for sharing, ehg
Great pics, Rob, & it was cool meting you & Glen!  Can't wait for the softwater, & we can    for some slimers....

nice post we were just east of you . The red honda van with all the   kids running around  had a blast , my nephew caught his first Fish thru the ice . Turned out to be on eof the top perch of the day at 9"  He went home happy with the remote control sled !  TB
